item.title: I am without words and filled with rage
item.description: And im also pissed off that epstien was super plugged in online and worked with Bannon to make these claims sound absolutely wild and unhinged to the point of lunacy to people who were not in the qanon cult to make it toxic to talk about. They wanted to make it so that if you told someone "the billionaire elites are kidnapping, trafficking, drugging, raping and killing kids for their amusement" they would think you are bit crazy and discredit all the other things you said. And it worked! At least for me. I would try to engage in debate with someone and the second they said anything about global child sex rings instilled listening and ended the conversation as fast as I could cuz obviously that person was crazy.... but they weren't crazy they were closer to the truth than I was. And now that its been made very fucking clear the things that happened and who was involved all I hear is crickets. Where are the crazy fuckers who show up to pizza shops with their guns to rescue kids trapped in a non existent basement? Where are the groups of armed people demanding to lidar every trump golf course and property to search for bodies? And not just trump, what about musk? Why is he allowed to still draw breath in this country? Why hasnt the rest of Texas stood up and stormed his.little SpaceX city and destroy everything that was built by a pedophile? We still have a lot to discuss and come to terms with, us on the left, q anon people, and centrists but goddamn I kinda figured a global network of billionaires raping and killing kids would be enough to unite us long enough to realize we dont have much differences and generally we all want the same stuff in life and if we work together we can get those things.
